FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - S. KOREA (18): (GYEONGSANGBUK-DO), BOVINE,
SUSPECTED, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
******************************************************************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Mon 31 Oct 2011
Source: Bloomberg News [edited]
http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-31/s-korea-discovers-suspected-case-of-foot-and-mouth-disease.html


South Korea discovered a suspected case of foot-and-mouth disease
[FMD] at a cattle farm in Pohang city, about 370 km (230 miles) from
Seoul, according to the agriculture ministry.

The owner of the farm reported to city officials earlier today [31 Oct
2011] that one of his 14 cattle showed symptoms, the Ministry of Food,
Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries said in an e-mailed statement. The
government is taking samples for testing and plans to announce the
results tomorrow morning [1 Nov 2011], it said.

The Asian nation killed about 9.7 million cattle, pigs and poultry
last winter [2010-2011] because of outbreaks of FMD and bird flu,
which helped fuel inflation and prompted an increase in meat imports.

[Byline: Sungwoo Park]

